00:42:01,860 --> 00:42:03,200
But it's spontaneous.

1147
00:42:03,500 --> 00:42:05,070
There's no magnetic field

1148
00:42:05,070 --> 00:42:06,640
pushing everything in that direction.

1149
00:42:06,820 --> 00:42:08,000
It just had to pick a direction.

1150
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:08,760
It picked a direction.

1151
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:11,280
It may be because of a tiny,

1152
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:11,680
tiny,

1153
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:13,540
tiny little stray magnetic field.

1154
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:16,360
But we're going to talk about it.

1155
00:42:16,420 --> 00:42:17,680
These are the things we're going to talk about.

1156
00:42:18,320 --> 00:42:21,300
And the point at which the symmetry is broken,

1157
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:23,860
the point at which the magnets tend

1158
00:42:23,860 --> 00:42:26,400
to line themselves up in some direction,

1159
00:42:26,660 --> 00:42:28,280
that's a phase transition.

1160
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:31,110
And that phase transition is

1161
00:42:31,110 --> 00:42:33,260
called the magnetic phase transition.

1162
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:35,520
All right.

1163
00:42:35,580 --> 00:42:37,300
So first of all,

1164
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:39,240
don't think about literal magnets,

1165
00:42:40,339 --> 00:42:45,059
because the model systems that

1166
00:42:45,059 --> 00:42:49,780
are studied often are quite unrealistic

1167
00:42:49,780 --> 00:42:51,300
as theories of physics.

1168
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:51,440
They're not really magnetic.

1169
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:53,540
They're just a bunch of ferromagnetic chunks of iron.

1170
00:42:55,060 --> 00:42:58,500
What makes them interesting is,

1171
00:42:58,500 --> 00:42:58,840
of course,

1172
00:42:58,860 --> 00:43:01,480
that they resemble a lot of other things in nature

1173
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:08,740
and that they're mathematically simple enough to study

1174
00:43:08,740 --> 00:43:10,490
and interesting enough to

1175
00:43:10,490 --> 00:43:12,240
exhibit features like phase transitions.

1176
00:43:12,480 --> 00:43:13,700
That's what makes them interesting.

1177
00:43:14,300 --> 00:43:14,940
OK.

1178
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:16,920
So let's start with the very,

1179
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:18,540
very simplest magnet.

1180
00:43:21,300 --> 00:43:21,480
As I say,

1181
00:43:21,480 --> 00:43:23,280
don't think of it as a real magnet.

1182
00:43:23,540 --> 00:43:25,550
This kind of magnet either

1183
00:43:25,550 --> 00:43:27,560
points up or it points down.

1184
00:43:27,780 --> 00:43:29,660
It doesn't get to point in random directions.

1185
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:32,310
You can think of it as

1186
00:43:32,310 --> 00:43:33,500
heads and tails if you like.

1187
00:43:33,940 --> 00:43:36,840
But this very simple mathematical magnet

1188
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:39,740
either points up or it points down.

1189
00:43:41,560 --> 00:43:43,140
So and we'll...

1190
00:43:45,060 --> 00:43:47,900
It doesn't matter how they're laid out on the blackboard,

1191
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:49,420
but let's lay them out and align.

1192
00:43:51,300 --> 00:43:53,080
Some of them are up.

1193
00:43:53,240 --> 00:43:54,500
Some of them are down.

1194
00:43:56,620 --> 00:43:59,580
And we want to make a statistical mechanics of this

1195
00:44:00,210 --> 00:44:02,945
and ask such questions of what's

1196
00:44:02,945 --> 00:44:05,680
the relative percentage of ups and downs,

1197
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:07,980
what's the energy of the magnet,

1198
00:44:07,980 --> 00:44:08,880
and so forth.

1199
00:44:09,620 --> 00:44:10,000
All right.

1200
00:44:10,020 --> 00:44:11,040
So before we begin,

1201
00:44:11,040 --> 00:44:13,300
if we're going to be talking about statistical mechanics

1202
00:44:13,300 --> 00:44:14,340
in the Boltzmann distribution,

1203
00:44:14,340 --> 00:44:17,060
we have to have an energy function.

1204
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:18,340
Remember,

1205
00:44:18,340 --> 00:44:20,100
e to the minus beta times the energy.

1206
00:44:20,100 --> 00:44:21,340
We have to know what the energy is.

1207
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:22,160
So,

1208
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:22,500
yeah.

1209
00:44:22,820 --> 00:44:24,260
When you say them,

1210
00:44:24,260 --> 00:44:27,260
do I think of these as particles or...

1211
00:44:27,260 --> 00:44:29,300
You can think of them as atoms in a crystal,

1212
00:44:29,300 --> 00:44:30,180
for example.

1213
00:44:30,520 --> 00:44:31,000
Yeah.

1214
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:33,500
You can think of them as atoms in a crystal.

1215
00:44:33,900 --> 00:44:38,440
The atoms have electrical currents or maybe they have spins.

1216
00:44:39,060 --> 00:44:41,600
Electrical currents make little electromagnets.

1217
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:43,850
And so each atom is a magnet

1218
00:44:43,850 --> 00:44:46,060
with a north pole and a south pole.

1219
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:49,680
But for the simplest model,

1220
00:44:50,100 --> 00:44:50,520
if you've ever studied,

1221
00:44:50,520 --> 00:44:53,080
which we're going to begin with,

1222
00:44:53,260 --> 00:44:56,480
the atoms point up or point down,

1223
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:58,380
and they can't point any other way.

1224
00:44:59,160 --> 00:44:59,800
And again,

1225
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:01,620
the purpose of this is to be simple.

1226
00:45:02,900 --> 00:45:03,340
Okay.

1227
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:04,200
So there's a lot of them.

1228
00:45:04,280 --> 00:45:04,920
How many of them?

1229
00:45:05,020 --> 00:45:05,880
Capital N.

1230
00:45:07,880 --> 00:45:09,100
And what is the energy?

1231
00:45:09,240 --> 00:45:10,580
We're going to start with a very,

1232
00:45:10,580 --> 00:45:12,280
very simple version.

1233
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:14,500
In the very simple version,

1234
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:18,360
there's no interaction between the atom,

1235
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:20,140
between the magnets at all,

1236
00:45:20,140 --> 00:45:23,120
but there is a magnetic field.

1237
00:45:24,060 --> 00:45:25,830
There's a magnetic field either

1238
00:45:25,830 --> 00:45:27,600
pointing up or pointing down.

1239
00:45:28,500 --> 00:45:31,900
I'm not sure which way my notes actually correspond to.

1240
00:45:32,140 --> 00:45:33,600
There's a magnetic field.

1241
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:36,400
Each atom has a magnetic moment.

1242
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:38,540
That's just a little number attached to it,

1243
00:45:38,580 --> 00:45:40,100
which tells you how strongly

1244
00:45:40,100 --> 00:45:41,620
it interacts with the magnetic field.

1245
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:44,100
It has a magnetic moment called mu.

1246
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:47,580
It has to do with...

1247
00:45:48,360 --> 00:45:49,360
with the strength of the magnet,

1248
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:49,820
basically.

1249
00:45:50,740 --> 00:45:52,180
There's a magnetic field.

1250
00:45:54,540 --> 00:45:57,120
The magnetic field is either pointing up or down,

1251
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:58,880
and I can't remember which way I chose it.

1252
00:45:59,020 --> 00:45:59,260
Well,

1253
00:45:59,260 --> 00:46:00,160
let's not worry about it.

1254
00:46:00,480 --> 00:46:03,160
But the energy of one of these magnets

1255
00:46:03,160 --> 00:46:05,840
is different if it's up or if it's down.

1256
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:07,480
In particular,

1257
00:46:07,480 --> 00:46:11,420
if the magnet is up,

1258
00:46:12,300 --> 00:46:15,880
I think we give it a plus energy,

1259
00:46:16,100 --> 00:46:18,060
and if the magnet is down,

1260
00:46:18,360 --> 00:46:19,280
we give it a minus energy.

1261
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:23,020
So let's invent a variable for each magnet.

1262
00:46:23,620 --> 00:46:24,720
Let's give it a name.

1263
00:46:24,780 --> 00:46:25,680
Let's call it sigma.

1264
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:28,500
This is the sigma for the first atom.

1265
00:46:28,720 --> 00:46:30,760
And this is sigma for the second atom.

1266
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:31,680
Blah,

1267
00:46:31,680 --> 00:46:31,800
blah,

1268
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:31,980
blah,

1269
00:46:31,980 --> 00:46:32,180
blah,

1270
00:46:32,180 --> 00:46:32,320
blah.

1271
00:46:32,460 --> 00:46:34,640
And sigma is either plus or minus one.

1272
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:38,760
It's just a label or a variable

1273
00:46:39,700 --> 00:46:42,380
which is plus or minus one.

1274
00:46:42,660 --> 00:46:44,720
So if the first spin is up,

1275
00:46:44,880 --> 00:46:48,020
that means sigma one is up.

1276
00:46:48,020 --> 00:46:48,520
It's plus.

1277
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:51,160
If the second spin is down,

1278
00:46:51,260 --> 00:46:53,300
it means sigma two is minus.

1279
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:54,840
And so forth.

1280
00:46:55,440 --> 00:46:55,920
Okay,

1281
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:57,640
what is the energy of this system?

1282
00:46:58,740 --> 00:47:00,520
If the spin is up,

1283
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:04,860
then the energy is positive,

1284
00:47:05,380 --> 00:47:07,580
and it's just equal to mu times h.

1285
00:47:10,200 --> 00:47:11,580
What if the spin is down?

1286
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:12,580
What's the energy then?

1287
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:14,480
Okay,

1288
00:47:14,480 --> 00:47:15,520
supposing there are n,

1289
00:47:15,660 --> 00:47:16,320
little n,

1290
00:47:16,320 --> 00:47:19,060
little n spins up,

1291
00:47:19,260 --> 00:47:21,640
and little m spins down.

1292
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:22,480
What's the energy?

1293
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:26,600
The energy is equal

1294
00:47:28,080 --> 00:47:31,940
to little n minus little m

1295
00:47:31,940 --> 00:47:34,720
times mu times h.

1296
00:47:36,400 --> 00:47:38,410
Mu times h is the energy

1297
00:47:38,410 --> 00:47:40,420
of one spin if it's up,

1298
00:47:41,160 --> 00:47:42,650
and minus mu times h

1299
00:47:42,650 --> 00:47:44,140
is the spin if it's down.

1300
00:47:44,140 --> 00:47:44,780
n,

1301
00:47:44,780 --> 00:47:46,600
little n,

1302
00:47:46,800 --> 00:47:49,920
equals the number of ups,

1303
00:47:50,660 --> 00:47:55,080
and little m is the number of downs.

1304
00:47:58,040 --> 00:48:00,560
What's little n plus little m?

1305
00:48:02,420 --> 00:48:03,200
Big N.

1306
00:48:04,220 --> 00:48:06,840
So little n plus little

1307
00:48:06,840 --> 00:48:09,460
m is equal to capital N.

1308
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:12,080
Okay,

1309
00:48:12,080 --> 00:48:13,040
we're good to go now.

1310
00:48:13,040 --> 00:48:15,020
We can write down the Boltzmann distribution,

1311
00:48:15,320 --> 00:48:17,040
and we can calculate anything we want

1312
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:18,300
using statistical mechanics.

1313
00:48:19,220 --> 00:48:20,980
So let's do that.

1314
00:48:21,420 --> 00:48:22,820
What are the dimensions,

1315
00:48:22,820 --> 00:48:23,200
please,

1316
00:48:23,240 --> 00:48:23,860
excuse me,

1317
00:48:23,860 --> 00:48:25,700
of h and e?

1318
00:48:26,260 --> 00:48:27,980
What are the dimensions?

1319
00:48:29,400 --> 00:48:29,820
I mean,

1320
00:48:29,820 --> 00:48:31,860
is h a number or a magnetic field?

1321
00:48:32,380 --> 00:48:33,220
For us,

1322
00:48:33,220 --> 00:48:33,640
it's a number.

1323
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:35,380
It's the strength of the magnetic field.

1324
00:48:37,180 --> 00:48:39,180
It's an external magnetic field

1325
00:48:39,180 --> 00:48:41,400
imposed on the magnet from outside.

1326
00:48:41,400 --> 00:48:43,480
So for our purposes,

1327
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:44,920
it's a number.

1328
00:48:46,680 --> 00:48:48,240
And mu is also a number.

1329
00:48:48,920 --> 00:48:52,460
And we might as well put mu and h together

1330
00:48:52,460 --> 00:48:54,720
and just call the whole thing a number.

1331
00:48:56,380 --> 00:48:57,340
That's often done.

1332
00:48:58,780 --> 00:49:00,260
Sometimes it's called little h,

1333
00:49:00,460 --> 00:49:01,960
but I thought I would just

1334
00:49:01,960 --> 00:49:03,460
expose the various pieces of it.

1335
00:49:05,060 --> 00:49:06,490
Would you prefer it called

1336
00:49:06,490 --> 00:49:07,920
big H times mu little h

1337
00:49:07,920 --> 00:49:09,560
and never see mu and the big H again?

1338
00:49:09,720 --> 00:49:10,540
We could do that.

1339
00:49:10,540 --> 00:49:11,100
It doesn't matter.

1340
00:49:11,340 --> 00:49:11,900
OK.

1341
00:49:13,180 --> 00:49:14,000
All right.

1342
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:14,960
Now...

1343
00:49:14,960 --> 00:49:15,600
Excuse me,

1344
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:16,080
what is e?

1345
00:49:17,600 --> 00:49:18,160
Oh,

1346
00:49:18,160 --> 00:49:18,480
sorry,

1347
00:49:18,480 --> 00:49:19,520
e equals...

1348
00:49:21,279 --> 00:49:22,160
This is the energy,

1349
00:49:22,160 --> 00:49:23,460
and it equals...

1350
00:49:23,460 --> 00:49:24,040
Good,

1351
00:49:24,040 --> 00:49:24,580
thank you.

1352
00:49:25,500 --> 00:49:27,020
Energy equals that.

1353
00:49:27,940 --> 00:49:28,500
OK.

1354
00:49:29,540 --> 00:49:30,100
Now,

1355
00:49:30,100 --> 00:49:32,680
how many configurations are there...

1356
00:49:33,600 --> 00:49:35,940
How many configurations are there

1357
00:49:37,760 --> 00:49:39,900
with little n ups

1358
00:49:40,540 --> 00:49:42,040
and little m downs?

1359
00:49:42,580 --> 00:49:44,680
Without asking which ones are which,

1360
00:49:45,419 --> 00:49:47,320
how many configurations are there?

1361
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:48,940
We have capital N things,

1362
00:49:49,560 --> 00:49:52,100
and we want to group them into two groups.

1363
00:49:53,760 --> 00:49:55,200
One group of little n

1364
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:56,640
and one group of little m.

1365
00:49:57,560 --> 00:50:00,140
How many such configurations are there?

1366
00:50:00,240 --> 00:50:01,780
How many such arrangements are there?

1367
00:50:02,640 --> 00:50:04,100
That's a combinatoric problem.

1368
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:05,240
All right.

1369
00:50:05,940 --> 00:50:06,460
Yeah.

1370
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:07,420
Yeah,

1371
00:50:07,420 --> 00:50:08,320
but let's write it down.

1372
00:50:08,320 --> 00:50:13,420
The number of configurations with this value of energy...

1373
00:50:13,420 --> 00:50:16,880
The number of configurations with this value of energy

1374
00:50:16,880 --> 00:50:20,380
is capital N factorial...

1375
00:50:21,140 --> 00:50:22,360
This is number...

1376
00:50:23,439 --> 00:50:24,560
Not mumber,

1377
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:24,880
number.

1378
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:30,220
Number of states...

1379
00:50:33,919 --> 00:50:36,780
for a given n minus m

1380
00:50:36,780 --> 00:50:38,600
is n factorial

1381
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:42,060
over little n factorial,

1382
00:50:42,060 --> 00:50:43,660
little m factorial,

1383
00:50:44,900 --> 00:50:46,810
remembering that little n and little

1384
00:50:46,810 --> 00:50:48,720
m add up to big N.

1385
00:50:49,820 --> 00:50:52,080
That's the number of such configurations.

1386
00:50:54,260 --> 00:50:55,040
All right.

1387
00:50:56,080 --> 00:50:58,280
Let's take one of those configurations

1388
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:01,000
and ask what the Boltzmann weight is for that.

1389
00:51:01,040 --> 00:51:02,590
The Boltzmann weight means e to

1390
00:51:02,590 --> 00:51:04,140
the minus beta times the energy.

1391
00:51:04,720 --> 00:51:05,500
All right.

1392
00:51:05,500 --> 00:51:06,220
In fact,

1393
00:51:06,220 --> 00:51:08,430
what we're going to be doing

1394
00:51:08,430 --> 00:51:10,640
