01:22:59,306 --> 01:23:01,886
Ground states mean states of minimum energy.

2277
01:23:02,866 --> 01:23:05,426
And they will both come in with equal probability.

2278
01:23:06,546 --> 01:23:06,986
And they're going to be aligned.

2279
01:23:06,986 --> 01:23:08,886
They'll both come in with equal probability.

2280
01:23:10,366 --> 01:23:13,066
But now let me add one more thing.

2281
01:23:13,786 --> 01:23:17,126
Let me suppose that there's a magnetic field,

2282
01:23:18,526 --> 01:23:20,246
external magnetic field,

2283
01:23:20,246 --> 01:23:23,606
but it's only acting on one particle.

2284
01:23:24,046 --> 01:23:26,876
One out of 10 to the

2285
01:23:26,876 --> 01:23:29,706
23rd has a little stray magnetic field.

2286
01:23:29,926 --> 01:23:33,706
And let's say that magnetic field is along one axis.

2287
01:23:33,866 --> 01:23:34,926
Then what is the ground state?

2288
01:23:34,926 --> 01:23:39,146
The ground state has a definite orientation.

2289
01:23:39,586 --> 01:23:42,546
Even if that magnetic field is very small,

2290
01:23:42,946 --> 01:23:45,846
the ground state still has a definite orientation.

2291
01:23:46,246 --> 01:23:47,826
And at zero temperature,

2292
01:23:47,826 --> 01:23:49,586
at strictly zero temperature,

2293
01:23:50,586 --> 01:23:54,046
the Boltzmann distribution always favors

2294
01:23:54,046 --> 01:23:57,506
infinitely strongly the lowest energy state.

2295
01:23:57,826 --> 01:24:03,106
So that means that even the tiniest little magnetic field,

2296
01:24:03,106 --> 01:24:04,506
stray magnetic field,

2297
01:24:04,546 --> 01:24:04,906
is going to be aligned with the ground state.

2298
01:24:04,906 --> 01:24:05,546
Well,

2299
01:24:05,546 --> 01:24:08,236
the Boltzmann distribution will favor all

2300
01:24:08,236 --> 01:24:10,926
of the spins pointing along one axis.

2301
01:24:11,846 --> 01:24:14,786
If you were to apply that tiny magnetic field,

2302
01:24:15,825 --> 01:24:19,045
let the system come to equilibrium at zero temperature,

2303
01:24:19,226 --> 01:24:20,946
and then remove the magnetic field,

2304
01:24:21,226 --> 01:24:22,786
the system will remember it.

2305
01:24:23,126 --> 01:24:25,286
Everybody's holding everybody else in place.

2306
01:24:25,546 --> 01:24:28,226
And the possibility of them all

2307
01:24:28,226 --> 01:24:30,906
simultaneously jumping to the opposite state

2308
01:24:30,906 --> 01:24:33,906
is remote if there's enough of them.

2309
01:24:34,906 --> 01:24:37,166
So that's called spontaneous symmetry breaking.

2310
01:24:37,386 --> 01:24:39,746
That is what spontaneous symmetry breaking is.

2311
01:24:39,966 --> 01:24:41,226
In this case,

2312
01:24:41,226 --> 01:24:41,806
it's very simple.

2313
01:24:41,886 --> 01:24:45,466
And this example has a symmetry.

2314
01:24:45,966 --> 01:24:48,986
We can actually say quantitatively

2315
01:24:48,986 --> 01:24:52,006
or mathematically what that symmetry is.

2316
01:24:52,726 --> 01:24:55,656
A symmetry is usually represented by a

2317
01:24:55,656 --> 01:24:58,586
