2318
01:24:59,546 --> 01:25:03,266
What mathematical operation would you do on sigma

2319
01:25:04,906 --> 01:25:05,866
if you were to change from up to down?

2320
01:25:09,586 --> 01:25:10,746
Multiply it by minus one.

2321
01:25:12,186 --> 01:25:12,706
Right.

2322
01:25:12,986 --> 01:25:13,506
Okay.

2323
01:25:13,706 --> 01:25:16,286
Let's go back to the earlier case over here,

2324
01:25:16,426 --> 01:25:17,686
where the energy,

2325
01:25:17,686 --> 01:25:19,406
in this case we could say,

2326
01:25:19,606 --> 01:25:22,706
the energy was proportional to just sigma itself,

2327
01:25:23,046 --> 01:25:24,686
not sigma times a neighboring sigma,

2328
01:25:24,926 --> 01:25:26,386
but just sigma by itself.

2329
01:25:26,746 --> 01:25:27,866
Does that have a symmetry?

2330
01:25:28,426 --> 01:25:28,946
No.

2331
01:25:29,006 --> 01:25:33,586
The energy itself changes sign when you change sigma.

2332
01:25:33,586 --> 01:25:34,366
And that's not a symmetry.

2333
01:25:34,406 --> 01:25:36,026
Symmetry is actions that you can

2334
01:25:36,026 --> 01:25:37,646
do that don't change the energy.

2335
01:25:38,726 --> 01:25:39,166
Okay.

2336
01:25:39,866 --> 01:25:41,006
What about this system?

2337
01:25:41,086 --> 01:25:43,166
Supposing you change the sign of one spin,

2338
01:25:43,166 --> 01:25:44,246
one of them,

2339
01:25:44,426 --> 01:25:45,806
sigma one and not sigma two.

2340
01:25:46,186 --> 01:25:47,106
Is that a symmetry?

2341
01:25:48,546 --> 01:25:48,986
No.

2342
01:25:49,026 --> 01:25:50,166
The energy changes.

2343
01:25:50,866 --> 01:25:52,106
But what if you change them both?

2344
01:25:53,546 --> 01:25:54,686
If you change them both,

2345
01:25:54,686 --> 01:25:56,986
then the energy doesn't change sign.

2346
01:25:57,346 --> 01:26:00,026
So if you go from two up to two down,

2347
01:26:00,026 --> 01:26:01,246
that's a symmetry.

2348
01:26:01,426 --> 01:26:03,566
Now we have this whole vast array of them,

2349
01:26:10,286 --> 01:26:14,126
and what if we change all of the sigmas simultaneously?

2350
01:26:14,646 --> 01:26:18,826
We write formally the equation sigma of i

2351
01:26:18,826 --> 01:26:23,006
for all i goes to minus sigma of i.

2352
01:26:24,906 --> 01:26:28,705
We replace every sigma by minus its value.

2353
01:26:28,905 --> 01:26:30,705
Then the energy doesn't change.

2354
01:26:31,606 --> 01:26:33,466
Then the energy doesn't change.

2355
01:26:33,466 --> 01:26:35,226
And that's what it means to have a symmetry,

2356
01:26:35,486 --> 01:26:37,866
an operation that you can do

2357
01:26:37,866 --> 01:26:40,246
on the coordinates of a system

2358
01:26:40,246 --> 01:26:42,086
that don't change the energy,

2359
01:26:42,086 --> 01:26:42,986
no matter what state,

2360
01:26:42,986 --> 01:26:43,886
for every state.

2361
01:26:44,106 --> 01:26:45,126
Whatever the state is,

2362
01:26:45,126 --> 01:26:49,006
there is another corresponding state

2363
01:26:49,806 --> 01:26:52,646
which has the same energy but

2364
01:26:52,646 --> 01:26:55,486
in which the spins are all reoriented

2365
01:26:55,486 --> 01:26:57,626
opposite to what you started with.

2366
01:26:58,646 --> 01:27:02,726
And that ensures that in some sense,

2367
01:27:02,726 --> 01:27:06,166
there's no bias to up or down.

2368
01:27:06,906 --> 01:27:10,116
If the system is going to flop

2369
01:27:10,116 --> 01:27:13,326
itself all simultaneously into up at zero temperature,

2370
01:27:13,586 --> 01:27:17,106
that means it could have also flopped itself into down.

2371
01:27:18,446 --> 01:27:20,426
There's no way to predict in advance,

2372
01:27:20,566 --> 01:27:23,746
unless you know that tiny little stray magnetic field,

2373
01:27:24,605 --> 01:27:26,115
there's no way to predict in

2374
01:27:26,115 --> 01:27:27,626
advance which way it's going to go,

2375
01:27:27,646 --> 01:27:29,046
but it's going to go one way or the other,

2376
01:27:29,126 --> 01:27:30,666
because the Boltzmann distribution says you've

2377
01:27:30,666 --> 01:27:32,206
got to be in the ground state.

2378
01:27:33,186 --> 01:27:33,756
So you've got to be in

2379
01:27:33,756 --> 01:27:34,326
the ground state for zero temperature.

2380
01:27:36,666 --> 01:27:37,946
And as I said,

2381
01:27:37,946 --> 01:27:40,386
the little tiny stray magnetic field,

2382
01:27:40,506 --> 01:27:42,186
which will determine which one it is,

2383
01:27:42,266 --> 01:27:43,326
but it will be one of them.

